==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glum
<hw>Glum</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Moody; silent; sullen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I frighten people by my <qex>glun</qex> face.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glum</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Glum
<hw>Glum</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To look sullen; to be of a sour
countenance; to be glum.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hawes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glumaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
